93
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:13,109
No. There is something about tonight
that wants a place like this.

94
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,993
It's where you end a holiday.

95
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:17,640
- You've been on a holiday?
- Sort of.

96
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,036
I don't much like holidays.

97
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,675
Poor baby.

98
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,472
Are you an orphan?

99
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,636
Yeah. I'm an orphan of destiny.

100
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:30,551
I see life in all its dirty details.

101
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:33,313
- You know how it is.
- Sure I know how it is.

102
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,431
- You had a hard day.
- You could say that.

103
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,511
And you'd like to relieve the stress.

104
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,432
Sounds like a good idea to me.

105
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:43,236
Only maybe you are confusing me
with another kind of woman.

106
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:47,199
No, I'm not confusing anything.

107
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,632
Maybe it's just me.

108
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:56,356
- I have to go.
- Wait. I thought we were doing good here.

109
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:00,396
- We were. Now I have to leave.
- Don't go, please.

110
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,751
- Let me start all over again.
- You started just fine.

111
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,513
In fact, you just about
swept me off my feet.

112
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,990
- I did?
- I said "just about."

113
