515
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:47,274
Go ahead.

516
00:58:47,560 --> 00:58:48,629
Thank you.

517
00:58:53,080 --> 00:58:55,469
Was your husband here alone
while you were away?

518
00:58:55,560 --> 00:58:56,629
Yes.

519
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:04,315
Did you notice anything funny
about the house when you came back?

520
00:59:04,440 --> 00:59:05,475
No.

521
00:59:09,760 --> 00:59:11,910
No open doors or windows?

522
00:59:13,120 --> 00:59:14,109
No.

523
00:59:16,840 --> 00:59:19,991
- How long has that been broken?
- A couple of weeks.

524
00:59:22,880 --> 00:59:25,110
They're easy enough to fix, you know.

525
00:59:28,360 --> 00:59:29,713
How'd it break?

526
00:59:30,360 --> 00:59:32,078
Closing it, I think.

527
00:59:32,640 --> 00:59:35,518
What kind of car was your husband driving,
ma'am?

528
00:59:35,680 --> 00:59:37,079
Black Buick.

529
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:57,511
- You want to canvas?
- Yeah.

530
00:59:57,680 --> 01:00:00,433
Let's take a look at the rest
of the house first.

531
01:00:01,880 --> 01:00:04,110
- Did you see how nervous she was?
- Was she?

532
01:00:04,200 --> 01:00:07,670
She was so tight you could have bounced
a golf ball off of her.

533
01:00:07,760 --> 01:00:10,479
The window was jammed. It didn't move.

534
01:00:11,160 --> 01:00:12,275
Yeah, so?

535
01:00:12,360 --> 01:00:13,839
She was lying.

536
01:00:15,280 --> 01:00:17,953
You think she was lying
about the rest of it?

537
01:00:18,040 --> 01:00:19,473
I don't know.

538
01:00:34,320 --> 01:00:36,515
- What's up?
- It's his car.

539
01:00:38,800 --> 01:00:40,199
It's clean.

540
01:00:41,160 --> 01:00:43,913
- How long's it been here?
- We don't know.

541
01:00:49,600 --> 01:00:51,431
Light bulb here is busted.

542
01:00:52,960 --> 01:00:54,996
Someone knew what they were doing.

543
01:01:21,720 --> 01:01:23,392
They'll want to see you again.

544
01:01:23,480 --> 01:01:25,596
- Why?
- They found his car.

545
01:01:25,680 --> 01:01:28,990
- They're going to ask you some questions.
- I'm scared.

546
01:01:29,840 --> 01:01:33,469
It's going to be okay.
You just got to stick with your story.

547
01:01:39,040 --> 01:01:40,792
She's a cuckoo bird.

548
01:01:42,280 --> 01:01:44,953
She's had psychiatric care
for four years off and on.

549
01:01:45,040 --> 01:01:48,476
She tried to commit suicide
with a mouth full of valiums...

550
01:01:48,600 --> 01:01:51,353
...and she's filed for divorce two times.

551
01:01:59,280 --> 01:02:03,319
Munro's car was wiped clean.
No fingerprints.

552
01:02:04,880 --> 01:02:08,236
If this was murder,
someone knew what they were doing.

553
01:02:08,880 --> 01:02:10,871
It wasn't no cuckoo bird.

554
01:02:13,200 --> 01:02:14,519
Good work.

555
01:02:21,360 --> 01:02:24,238
Will you please state your name
and present address?

556
01:02:24,360 --> 01:02:28,035
Mrs. Rachel Munro.
I live at 201 Cypress Avenue.

557
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:32,753
The evening we were called
to your residence, July 17...

558
01:02:32,840 --> 01:02:34,592
...did your husband strike you?

559
01:02:34,680 --> 01:02:35,874
I guess he did.

560
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:37,029
Why?

561
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,313
I don't know.

562
01:02:40,040 --> 01:02:41,871
We have arguments sometimes.

563
01:02:42,320 --> 01:02:46,438
- What was the argument on that night?
- You don't have to answer that.

564
01:02:47,720 --> 01:02:51,508
My husband was accusing me
of having an extramarital affair.

565
01:02:51,840 --> 01:02:53,068
Had you?

566
01:02:53,720 --> 01:02:56,473
Mr. Dickey, my client is here
to make a statement...

567
01:02:56,560 --> 01:02:59,836
...regarding where she was at the time,
not her sexual druthers.

568
01:03:00,920 --> 01:03:04,390
- How many times did he strike you?
- It wasn't much of anything.

569
01:03:04,760 --> 01:03:08,753
In Detective Bodine's report,
it states there are clear signs...

570
01:03:08,840 --> 01:03:10,239
...of physical abuse.

571
01:03:10,320 --> 01:03:11,514
A slap.

572
01:03:15,680 --> 01:03:18,558
What happened after Detective Dickey
and I left your home?

573
01:03:18,640 --> 01:03:22,189
I slept on the side porch,
and in the morning I called a taxi.

574
01:03:22,280 --> 01:03:26,558
It took me to the airport,
and I took a 10:00 flight to Miami.

575
01:03:27,080 --> 01:03:30,311
You were there Thursday through Sunday,
returning Monday morning.

576
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:31,469
Yes.

577
01:03:32,080 --> 01:03:34,594
Did you call your husband from the hotel?

578
01:03:35,200 --> 01:03:36,189
No.

579
01:03:37,720 --> 01:03:39,233
I wanted to be alone.

580
01:03:39,480 --> 01:03:41,630
- Did you call anyone else?
- No.

581
01:03:42,160 --> 01:03:45,914
- You returned Monday the 22nd, right?
- Right.

582
01:03:46,680 --> 01:03:49,558
- What time did you arrive?
- About 11:00.

583
01:03:49,640 --> 01:03:52,154
- Did you call anyone when you got home?
- Yes.

584
01:03:52,240 --> 01:03:53,355
Who did you call?

585
01:03:53,440 --> 01:03:55,874
- The first person?
- Yeah.

586
01:03:57,000 --> 01:03:59,275
I phoned my husband's office.

587
01:04:00,200 --> 01:04:01,758
I spoke to his secretary.

588
01:04:01,840 --> 01:04:03,398
Who else did you call?

589
01:04:04,480 --> 01:04:05,549
No one.

590
01:04:06,480 --> 01:04:11,315
I thought if your husband was the first,
there would have been someone else.

591
01:04:12,720 --> 01:04:14,551
There was no one else.

592
01:04:15,960 --> 01:04:19,236
Saturday night before your husband
was first missed...

593
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:23,998
...a neighbour noticed your houselights
were on until 3:00 in the morning.

594
01:04:24,080 --> 01:04:26,958
- Could someone have been there?
- I don't know.

595
01:04:32,520 --> 01:04:36,672
Mrs. Munro, we're going to want
to take another look at the house.

596
01:04:49,160 --> 01:04:50,878
- Are they inside?
- Yeah.

597
01:04:51,360 --> 01:04:53,999
Maybe they'll find him under the bed.

598
01:04:55,840 --> 01:04:59,833
- Where was she?
- She was in Miami at the Registry Hotel.

599
01:05:01,520 --> 01:05:04,114
Checked in Thursday last,
checked out Monday morning.

600
01:05:04,200 --> 01:05:07,988
Now, Saturday night at 9:37,
she called her husband here...

601
01:05:08,840 --> 01:05:10,910
...and got him just before he went out.

602
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:14,959
At 11:41 p.m., she called him again
at the Brayton Country Club.

603
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:17,235
She said she didn't call anyone
from the hotel.

604
01:05:17,320 --> 01:05:19,072
Yeah, that's what she said.

605
01:05:19,800 --> 01:05:20,789
Sunday...

606
01:05:22,360 --> 01:05:26,478
...at 10:00 a.m., she had brunch poolside.
Stayed there all day.

607
01:05:26,600 --> 01:05:30,070
They got her signature and everything.
What do you think?

608
01:05:30,560 --> 01:05:31,788
I don't know.

609
01:05:31,880 --> 01:05:33,518
She was in Miami.

610
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:36,717
Maybe she got one of her lover-boys
to kill him.

611
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:38,552
Maybe. Maybe you're guessing.

612
01:05:40,480 --> 01:05:41,595
No, I'm not.

613
01:05:42,320 --> 01:05:45,949
Hell, everybody knows.
She's going to get a load of dough.

614
01:05:46,360 --> 01:05:49,113
Don't it bother you
how come she's so nervous?

615
01:05:49,200 --> 01:05:50,952
You think she's nervous?

616
01:05:53,120 --> 01:05:54,678
Who do you think she is?

617
01:05:54,760 --> 01:05:57,991
She's got a reputation all over town
for having her way with men.

618
01:05:58,080 --> 01:06:00,674
- Is that so?
- I've heard stories here.

619
01:06:01,760 --> 01:06:03,557
What kind of stories?

620
01:06:03,760 --> 01:06:07,070
She used to entertain men
when her husband was away.

621
01:06:08,280 --> 01:06:10,475
- Who told you that?
- Come on, Kyle.

622
01:06:10,560 --> 01:06:12,278
What do you think is going on here?

623
01:06:12,360 --> 01:06:15,477
There was nothing in the car,
not a fingerprint.

624
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:17,438
Rupert Munro was a big guy.

625
01:06:17,520 --> 01:06:19,875
So wherever he went,
somebody carried him.

626
01:06:19,960 --> 01:06:23,350
You know she got one of her lover-boys
to come over here and kill him.

627
01:06:23,440 --> 01:06:26,273
- Where would they put the body?
- You tell me.

628
01:06:27,920 --> 01:06:30,354
It was raining so hard that night.

629
01:06:31,080 --> 01:06:34,277
No one is going to dig a hole
in the mud and rain.

630
01:06:37,960 --> 01:06:39,473
- Hello, sugar.
- Hi.

631
01:06:39,720 --> 01:06:43,110
- Thanks a lot. How's it going inside?
- We haven't found anything yet.

632
01:06:43,200 --> 01:06:44,519
All right.

633
01:06:48,280 --> 01:06:49,793
Here she comes.

634
01:06:52,760 --> 01:06:56,116
I brought you some lemonade.
It's fresh. I made it this morning.

635
01:06:56,200 --> 01:06:58,395
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

636
01:07:01,240 --> 01:07:04,038
- Who was in your hotel room in Miami?
- <i>What?</i>

637
01:07:05,400 --> 01:07:09,313
- Who called Munro from your room?
- <i>/ don't know what you're ta/king about.</i>

638
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:10,833
You know.

639
01:07:10,920 --> 01:07:12,956
You put someone there.
You came to kill him.

640
01:07:13,040 --> 01:07:14,029
<i>/ didn't.</i>

641
01:07:14,120 --> 01:07:16,998
- Tell me the truth, goddamn it.
- <i>P/ease, / am.</i>

642
01:07:19,400 --> 01:07:20,913
<i>Nobody was there.</i>

643
01:07:22,800 --> 01:07:24,313
Somebody's lying.

644
01:07:24,960 --> 01:07:26,791
This doesn't make any sense.

645
01:07:31,720 --> 01:07:32,709
Kyle.

646
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:34,673
Just got a call.

647
01:07:34,800 --> 01:07:38,236
Someone saw a car last week
parked out by Camelia Lake at night.

648
01:07:38,840 --> 01:07:39,875
Shiny black car.

649
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:41,871
- Who made the call?
- Anonymous.

650
01:07:56,760 --> 01:07:58,113
<i>Find anything?</i>

651
01:07:58,400 --> 01:07:59,879
Can't see anything.

652
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:02,550
<i>We got nothing. We're coming in.</i>

653
01:08:02,720 --> 01:08:04,517
Maybe we'll have to come back.

654
01:08:04,600 --> 01:08:06,875
- Do you think it's here?
- I don't know.

655
01:08:08,840 --> 01:08:10,319
I need a hand.

656
01:08:11,480 --> 01:08:12,595
So that's it.

657
01:08:12,680 --> 01:08:16,070
<i>Wait. / think we got something.</i>

658
01:08:16,840 --> 01:08:18,990
<i>Oh, Jesus, / think we got him.</i>

659
01:08:53,040 --> 01:08:54,632
I think it's him.

660
01:08:55,840 --> 01:08:58,149
You got yourself a big old murder, Kyle.

661
01:09:06,520 --> 01:09:11,719
From the patent decomposition of the body
and water temperature of 72 degrees...

662
01:09:11,960 --> 01:09:16,317
...it is estimated the deceased has been
in the water for a period of seven days.

663
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:17,389
Last Saturday.

664
01:09:17,480 --> 01:09:21,029
Body evidence is two gunshot wounds,
medium thoracic perforating...

665
01:09:21,120 --> 01:09:25,830
...the lower third of the sternum.
Evidence of slight powder flaking.

666
01:09:26,280 --> 01:09:30,193
No evidence of exit wound.
Second wound is above the right eye.

667
01:09:30,920 --> 01:09:33,798
Patent evidence
of powder and gas scorching.

668
01:09:34,280 --> 01:09:37,556
Exit wound lateral to second vertebra.

669
01:09:41,480 --> 01:09:43,630
You're going to get a bullet.

670
01:09:46,160 --> 01:09:48,355
A bit smashed up, but a bullet.

671
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,073
May I?

672
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:01,315
Let me see.

673
01:10:06,280 --> 01:10:07,633
Looks like a.38.

674
01:10:07,800 --> 01:10:10,360
Yeah, maybe nine millimetre.
Practically the same.

675
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:11,839
Let's measure it.

676
01:10:12,640 --> 01:10:14,437
Lee, can I have the calliper?

677
01:10:16,800 --> 01:10:18,233
Thanks.

678
01:10:28,080 --> 01:10:29,274
.38.

679
01:10:32,360 --> 01:10:33,713
Something wrong?

680
01:10:36,800 --> 01:10:38,119
What's wrong?

681
01:10:42,720 --> 01:10:44,790
Nothing. It's a.38.

682
01:10:49,640 --> 01:10:51,915
- Here's a surprise for you.
- What?

683
01:10:52,920 --> 01:10:55,195
- There's water in the lungs.
- So?

684
01:10:56,040 --> 01:10:59,828
Two gunshots wounds in him,
and he was alive at the bottom the lake.

685
01:10:59,960 --> 01:11:02,599
Cause of death: Asphyxiation by drowning.

686
01:11:13,480 --> 01:11:14,674
Kyle.

687
01:11:18,480 --> 01:11:20,596
Look what's stuck in the heel of his shoe.

688
01:11:20,680 --> 01:11:22,318
- What is it?
- Glass.

689
01:11:30,280 --> 01:11:34,068
I can't be sure yet, but this looks like
the original Victorian glass.

690
01:11:34,240 --> 01:11:37,232
I think it's the same kind
you found on Munro's shoe.

691
01:11:37,320 --> 01:11:39,629
- This is where it happened.
- Maybe.

692
01:11:40,640 --> 01:11:43,029
Her lover-boy or someone came in.

693
01:11:43,440 --> 01:11:44,873
There was a struggle.

694
01:11:44,960 --> 01:11:47,520
The victim was hit in the head
and shot twice.

695
01:11:47,600 --> 01:11:49,875
Thinking he killed him,
he took him to the lake...

696
01:11:49,960 --> 01:11:51,712
...and dropped the car.

697
01:11:52,560 --> 01:11:56,633
We have no fingerprints in the whole place.
He knew what he was doing.

698
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:58,791
He wiped the place clean.

699
01:11:59,760 --> 01:12:03,435
I think he ran the damn humidifier
to melt down the prints.

700
01:12:04,280 --> 01:12:06,032
We'll find a print somewhere.

701
01:12:06,120 --> 01:12:08,714
We should. We know he was here.

702
01:12:45,440 --> 01:12:47,590
Kyle, we found something.

703
01:12:51,480 --> 01:12:53,516
My, my. Look what we got here.

704
01:12:59,440 --> 01:13:00,793
Dig it out.

705
01:13:07,120 --> 01:13:09,429
Well, Kyle, you were right.

706
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:12,836
Sooner or later, they all fuck up.

707
01:13:35,000 --> 01:13:36,194
Look at that.

708
01:13:36,800 --> 01:13:39,598
A perfect.38. Look at them riflings.

709
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:43,839
It will be easy to match this to a gun.

710
01:13:44,600 --> 01:13:46,477
All we need now is the gun.

711
01:14:03,760 --> 01:14:05,716
Who was with you in Miami?

712
01:14:06,880 --> 01:14:08,233
I was alone.

713
01:14:10,520 --> 01:14:12,954
You been sleeping with anyone
other than me?

714
01:14:13,040 --> 01:14:14,029
No.

715
01:14:16,000 --> 01:14:17,718
Why are you asking me this?

716
01:14:19,080 --> 01:14:21,514
I have been hearing things about you.

717
01:14:22,400 --> 01:14:24,391
Don't let them do this, Kyle.

718
01:14:24,800 --> 01:14:28,679
You said that they would try to change
your mind, and now they're doing it.

719
01:14:30,120 --> 01:14:31,155
Where's the gun?

720
01:14:31,240 --> 01:14:33,629
- What gun?
- The gun you shot him with.

721
01:14:33,720 --> 01:14:36,951
- You threw it away at the truck stop.
- That was a nine millimetre.

722
01:14:37,040 --> 01:14:38,314
I know.

723
01:14:40,440 --> 01:14:41,714
What are you saying?

724
01:14:41,800 --> 01:14:45,110
The bullet they took out of your husband's
body was shot from a.38.

725
01:14:45,200 --> 01:14:48,431
The bullet they took out of the wall today
was a.38.

726
01:14:48,520 --> 01:14:51,796
But I shot him with a nine millimetre.
You saw it.

727
01:14:56,840 --> 01:15:00,037
This is the bullet that was taken out
of the wall at Munro's house.

728
01:15:00,120 --> 01:15:03,396
This is the bullet that was taken out
of Munro's body.

729
01:15:03,600 --> 01:15:07,832
The riflings match perfectly.
They were both fired from the same gun.

730
01:15:09,320 --> 01:15:12,153
What are the pits on the bullets
that came out of Munro?

731
01:15:12,240 --> 01:15:13,673
I don't know.

732
01:15:14,320 --> 01:15:16,709
Sand will pit a bullet like that, won't it?

733
01:15:16,800 --> 01:15:21,669
The human body, as wonderful as it is,
contains one and half percent calcium...

734
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:26,118
...one percent potassium,
65 percent water, and after 5:00...

735
01:15:26,240 --> 01:15:29,357
...somewhat all percentage of alcohol.
But no sand.

736
01:16:04,240 --> 01:16:06,993
- Thank you very much for your help.
- Anytime.

737
01:16:11,200 --> 01:16:12,315
Kyle.

738
01:16:13,480 --> 01:16:15,357
The captain wants to talk to you.

739
01:16:15,440 --> 01:16:18,318
- What about?
- Something about the Munro case.

740
01:16:22,920 --> 01:16:25,309
Kyle, now were you seeing her?

741
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:26,989
No.

742
01:16:27,200 --> 01:16:29,714
You never went to see her alone
in her house?

743
01:16:29,960 --> 01:16:31,188
No, sir.

744
01:16:31,640 --> 01:16:33,596
You all were called out there, weren't you?

745
01:16:33,680 --> 01:16:36,035
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah, a couple of times.

746
01:16:36,520 --> 01:16:41,514
Her husband filed a complaint with us.
He said you used abusive language.

747
01:16:44,360 --> 01:16:45,918
Did you say that?

748
01:16:47,200 --> 01:16:48,952
He didn't say nothing, Captain.

749
01:16:49,080 --> 01:16:50,513
The guy was a jerk.

750
01:16:52,000 --> 01:16:53,433
This is a lie.

751
01:16:54,320 --> 01:16:57,790
- What was this, domestic violence call?
- Yes, sir.

752
01:16:59,000 --> 01:17:02,231
You took a special interest in this one,
didn't you?

753
01:17:02,480 --> 01:17:03,993
No, not really.

754
01:17:05,960 --> 01:17:09,475
Where were you a week ago
Saturday night, Kyle?

755
01:17:13,800 --> 01:17:15,279
I was at home.

756
01:17:15,920 --> 01:17:20,596
- Munro was shot with a.38, wasn't he?
- According to the autopsy report, yeah.

757
01:17:21,160 --> 01:17:24,755
- You carry a.38 special, don't you, Kyle?
- You know I do.

758
01:17:25,880 --> 01:17:27,233
May I see it?

759
01:17:40,440 --> 01:17:42,635
- You fire this recently?
- Yes, I have.

760
01:17:43,720 --> 01:17:46,598
We recovered a bullet
from that bedroom wall.

761
01:17:47,240 --> 01:17:49,390
The rifling marks are clean.

762
01:17:49,800 --> 01:17:52,678
It won't be too hard to tell
if it came from your gun.

763
01:17:52,760 --> 01:17:57,151
I'm putting you on administrative leave
until such time as we know that.

764
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:15,595
'Morning.

765
01:18:38,480 --> 01:18:41,074
Sorry, Kyle.
You're going to have to come with us.

766
01:18:41,160 --> 01:18:43,310
- What's going on?
- You tell me.

767
01:18:43,520 --> 01:18:45,988
You're the one who gave him
the wrong gun.

768
01:18:47,000 --> 01:18:49,673
- What are you talking about?
- Wrong serial number.

769
01:18:49,760 --> 01:18:53,833
You didn't give him your gun.
The captain wants to see you again.

770
01:18:57,320 --> 01:18:59,231
I'll be right with you.

771
01:19:16,440 --> 01:19:18,112
I got to tell you, Kyle.

772
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:22,671
A lot of people are upset and can't believe
you've done something like this.

773
01:19:32,840 --> 01:19:35,593
- Did you see her socially at any time?
- No.

774
01:19:37,400 --> 01:19:41,075
The night you met her, the bartender
showed you a credit card receipt...

775
01:19:41,160 --> 01:19:42,479
...with her name on it.

776
01:19:42,560 --> 01:19:46,075
- Did you call her or contact her in any way?
- No.

777
01:19:46,440 --> 01:19:48,590
She wasn't calling you here at the office?

778
01:19:48,680 --> 01:19:49,715
No.

779
01:19:50,200 --> 01:19:51,428
Who was?

780
01:19:52,560 --> 01:19:55,120
I don't know what calls
you're talking about.

781
01:19:55,600 --> 01:19:58,239
What are you protecting her for, Kyle?

782
01:19:59,720 --> 01:20:04,714
Where's this service revolver signed out
by you, serial number 0876B?

783
01:20:07,120 --> 01:20:09,190
I told you. I don't know.

784
01:20:09,400 --> 01:20:11,868
- Someone took yours, Kyle?
- Maybe.

785
01:20:12,520 --> 01:20:15,671
- Who would that have been?
- I don't know.

786
01:20:16,760 --> 01:20:19,877
- You never went to her house to see her?
- No.

787
01:20:21,080 --> 01:20:22,672
Smarten up, Kyle.

788
01:20:23,000 --> 01:20:25,639
You're going to fry for this
and she is going to walk.

789
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:29,030
That must've been what she had in mind
all along. Don't you think?

790
01:20:29,120 --> 01:20:33,159
We find your gun or any evidence
that puts you there and you're gone.

791
01:20:34,120 --> 01:20:37,874
Unless of course, you want to help us.

792
01:20:40,760 --> 01:20:41,749
Kyle.

793
01:20:43,160 --> 01:20:44,752
She's going to walk.

794
01:20:46,200 --> 01:20:47,758
She'll be real rich.

795
01:20:48,880 --> 01:20:51,189
She's going to get $12 million.

796
01:20:54,080 --> 01:20:57,231
The state attorney will cut a deal with you.

797
01:20:58,680 --> 01:21:01,114
You could be out in a couple of years.

798
01:22:03,640 --> 01:22:04,789
Is that you?

799
01:22:07,880 --> 01:22:10,678
- You got my money, Lamar?
- You got the ticket?

800
01:22:11,000 --> 01:22:12,513
Let me see it.

801
01:22:20,000 --> 01:22:22,468
You'll get the rest when I get mine.

802
01:22:33,320 --> 01:22:36,596
How much did you pay Dickey
to follow your husband?

803
01:22:47,040 --> 01:22:48,439
What is he to you?

804
01:22:50,560 --> 01:22:52,232
Rachel, start talking.

805
01:22:54,600 --> 01:22:57,398
Rupert was going to leave me
with nothing.

806
01:22:59,040 --> 01:23:01,315
Lamar told me how to do it all.

807
01:23:01,400 --> 01:23:02,913
How to do what?

808
01:23:03,880 --> 01:23:05,757
Set up Rupert's death...

809
01:23:07,480 --> 01:23:10,552
...where to meet you, the gun, Miami.

810
01:23:12,720 --> 01:23:14,073
Everything.

811
01:23:17,560 --> 01:23:19,551
- So we were just a lie?
- No.

812
01:23:21,400 --> 01:23:22,879
It changed, Kyle.

813
01:23:25,040 --> 01:23:26,837
It changed after I met you.

814
01:23:29,200 --> 01:23:31,475
I came back from Miami to be with you.

815
01:23:31,960 --> 01:23:35,077
You didn't even check out of the hotel.
You came back to kill him.

816
01:23:35,160 --> 01:23:37,037
No. We were going away.

817
01:23:37,320 --> 01:23:40,517
- Who made the phone calls from the room?
- Lamar put somebody there.

818
01:23:40,600 --> 01:23:42,875
- Who made the phone calls?
- I don't know.

819
01:23:42,960 --> 01:23:45,030
I just want to know the truth. Tell me!

820
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:46,235
I am.

821
01:23:49,440 --> 01:23:52,193
Don't look at me like that, Kyle, please.

822
01:23:52,280 --> 01:23:54,953
- I'm not a stranger to you.
- Yes, you are.

823
01:23:55,440 --> 01:23:56,714
Don't say that.

824
01:23:57,640 --> 01:23:59,915
- I love you.
- I don't want to hear it.

825
01:24:00,000 --> 01:24:02,116
- My life was over till I met you.
- Stop it!

826
01:24:02,200 --> 01:24:03,349
- I love you.
- Stop it!

827
01:24:03,440 --> 01:24:04,475
I love you!

828
01:24:04,560 --> 01:24:07,836
Then why didn't you tell me?
If you love me, why didn't you tell me?

829
01:24:07,920 --> 01:24:11,037
- I would've lost you for good.
- I don't want to hear more lies.

830
01:24:11,120 --> 01:24:12,109
No more lying.

831
01:24:12,200 --> 01:24:14,668
You were just fucking me, weren't you?

832
01:24:14,840 --> 01:24:17,798
I was loving you, and you were fucking me.

833
01:24:25,960 --> 01:24:27,871
You should have told me
from the beginning.

834
01:24:27,960 --> 01:24:29,791
Why didn't you just tell me?

835
01:24:30,440 --> 01:24:32,112
I tried to get out of it.

836
01:24:33,920 --> 01:24:35,592
Please believe me.

837
01:24:42,920 --> 01:24:44,273
Call Lamar.

838
01:24:46,280 --> 01:24:49,238
Tell him you want to see him
at JJ's tonight.

839
01:25:28,120 --> 01:25:29,473
Hello, Dickey-boy.

840
01:25:31,400 --> 01:25:32,389
Kyle.

841
01:25:33,720 --> 01:25:38,111
- You're a big disappointment to me.
- There was nothing I could do for you.

842
01:25:38,840 --> 01:25:40,159
Maybe not.

843
01:25:43,160 --> 01:25:47,153
You know, you figured this one
like you knew it all along.

844
01:25:50,040 --> 01:25:53,430
Yeah. I went to school on you, Kyle.

845
01:25:53,760 --> 01:25:54,795
You sure did.

846
01:25:54,880 --> 01:25:57,110
I listened to everything you told me.

847
01:25:58,000 --> 01:25:59,558
I knew you did it.

848
01:26:08,960 --> 01:26:11,394
You made too many mistakes, Lamar.

849
01:26:12,640 --> 01:26:14,756
What are you talking about?

850
01:26:16,600 --> 01:26:18,352
You took this, didn't you?

851
01:26:19,240 --> 01:26:20,878
I don't see my name on it.

852
01:26:20,960 --> 01:26:23,349
You see the compass on your dash?

853
01:26:29,800 --> 01:26:31,995
How did you know
about the $12 million trust?

854
01:26:32,080 --> 01:26:34,753
- Did she tell you?
- Why would she do that?

855
01:26:34,840 --> 01:26:37,195
Maybe you were going to help her
kill her husband.

856
01:26:37,280 --> 01:26:39,236
I didn't. You did.

857
01:26:40,720 --> 01:26:43,837
Well, you're going to jail with me anyway
because of this.

858
01:26:43,920 --> 01:26:45,239
You see...

859
01:26:45,680 --> 01:26:48,592
...it's all pitted from sand...

860
01:26:51,040 --> 01:26:54,112
...just like the bullet
they took out of Munro.

861
01:26:55,040 --> 01:26:59,158
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- You switched my gun, didn't you? My.38.

862
01:26:59,240 --> 01:27:01,800
You shot it in the sand,
and then you got the bullet...

863
01:27:01,920 --> 01:27:04,115
...in the autopsy room
when nobody was looking.

864
01:27:04,200 --> 01:27:08,352
You switched it with the nine millimetre
slug they pulled out of Munro's chest.

865
01:27:10,520 --> 01:27:12,158
No one is going to believe that.

866
01:27:12,240 --> 01:27:16,279
You fired my.38 into the wall at Munro's
house, so the slug from the wall...

867
01:27:16,360 --> 01:27:20,194
...and the slug from the body match.
And they're both from my gun.

868
01:27:21,120 --> 01:27:23,793
You got a desperate imagination, my man.

869
01:27:27,800 --> 01:27:29,950
How did you know where the body was?

870
01:27:32,000 --> 01:27:33,752
Did she tell you?

871
01:27:34,840 --> 01:27:37,115
- What do you think?
- I don't know.

872
01:27:39,200 --> 01:27:42,636
All you got to do is get the mileage
from the car...

873
01:27:43,240 --> 01:27:45,879
...and you know how far away the lake is.

874
01:27:51,760 --> 01:27:55,548
- Get up, you son of a bitch.
- Don't fuck yourself up worse, Kyle.

875
01:27:56,360 --> 01:27:57,918
Let's go.

876
01:28:09,360 --> 01:28:10,713
Sit down.

877
01:28:11,840 --> 01:28:13,717
I told him everything, Lamar.

878
01:28:16,600 --> 01:28:18,033
Where's my gun?

879
01:28:20,200 --> 01:28:21,758
I don't have it, Kyle.

880
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:25,437
Give me the goddamn gun.

881
01:28:27,040 --> 01:28:28,314
It's in my car.

882
01:28:41,760 --> 01:28:46,072
If you've cooked up something, Lamar,
I'll blow your fucking head off.

883
01:28:48,120 --> 01:28:52,033
Let's go outside. Get up. Let's go.
Wait for me, Rachel.

884
01:28:58,760 --> 01:28:59,636
Move.

885
01:28:59,720 --> 01:29:01,950
- Are you going to shoot me?
- Lf I have to.

886
01:29:02,040 --> 01:29:03,792
Well, you won't have to.

887
01:29:04,120 --> 01:29:06,395
- How much were you in for?
- A lot.

888
01:29:06,640 --> 01:29:08,358
The lady was desperate.

889
01:29:08,520 --> 01:29:11,592
Then she wanted to call it off,
but the money smelled too good.

890
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:15,036
Why me?
Why not some fucking bozo off the street?

891
01:29:15,120 --> 01:29:17,953
- Why'd you set up your own partner?
- It had to be you.

892
01:29:18,040 --> 01:29:20,031
You would've cracked the case
and busted me.

893
01:29:20,320 --> 01:29:21,639
You got that right.

894
01:29:21,720 --> 01:29:23,950
But you know what?
You were never the fall guy.

895
01:29:24,040 --> 01:29:25,029
You were my insurance.

896
01:29:25,120 --> 01:29:28,795
Fuck you, Dickey-boy. You screwed up.
First the pictures, then my.38.

897
01:29:28,880 --> 01:29:31,553
You kept it too long. Open it up.

898
01:29:35,600 --> 01:29:36,953
Come on.

899
01:29:39,680 --> 01:29:40,715
Where is it?

900
01:29:40,800 --> 01:29:42,756
Under the driver's seat.

901
01:29:49,320 --> 01:29:51,515
- It's not too late, Kyle.
- Shut up.

902
01:29:53,200 --> 01:29:55,953
Toss the gun in the lake.
You can forget it ever happened.

903
01:29:56,040 --> 01:29:57,268
Shut up.

904
01:29:58,680 --> 01:30:01,353
- Police! Stop right there!
- He's got a gun!

905
01:30:06,400 --> 01:30:07,389
Kyle!

906
01:30:21,080 --> 01:30:23,355
Kyle?

907
01:30:26,000 --> 01:30:27,194
Stay with me.

908
01:30:28,320 --> 01:30:29,833
Stay with me.

909
01:30:31,040 --> 01:30:32,598
I was never...

910
01:30:33,280 --> 01:30:34,918
...going to leave you.

911
01:30:41,640 --> 01:30:42,629
No.

912
01:30:44,920 --> 01:30:45,909
No!

913
01:31:15,800 --> 01:31:16,994
Rachel.

914
01:31:20,880 --> 01:31:22,108
Kyle was right.

915
01:31:23,800 --> 01:31:26,553
Sooner or later, they all fuck up.

